title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.CHANGE_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to change the state of network connectivity.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

com.comcast.hsf.permission.C2D_MESSAGE.description: Allows the application to receive push notifications.

android.permission.INSTALL_PACKAGES.description: Allows an application to install new or updated Android packages. Malicious applications can use this to add new applications with arbitrarily powerful permissions.

android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to connect to and disconnect from Wi-Fi access points and to make changes to configured Wi-Fi networks.

android.permission.WRITE_SETTINGS.description: Allows an application to modify the system's settings data. Malicious applications can corrupt your system's configuration.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.BROADCAST_STICKY.description: Allows an application to send sticky broadcasts, which remain after the broadcast ends. Malicious applications can make the phone slow or unstable by causing it to use too much memory.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.GET_TASKS.description: Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to the SD card.

android.permission.REQUEST_INSTALL_PACKA.info: Allows an application to request installing packages.
android.permission.REQUEST_INSTALL_PACKA.description: Malicious applications can use this to try and trick users into installing additional malicious packages.

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.bsgwireless.fac.BootStrapActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

Broadcast Receiver (com.google.android.gms.gcm.GcmReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: com.google.android.c2dm.permission.SEND
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

"connect_faq_answer_1" : "1. Select a Wi-Fi network (also referred to as an SSID) from within the app 'Network Selection' Screen or your device's system Wi-Fi settings. 

2. If you select from the device system settings and have Auto Connect enabled (from within the 'Settings' view), you will see a notification at the top of the screen and will be connected automatically.  

3. If you do not have Auto Connect enabled, simply launch this app and tap 'Connect' from the side menu. Getting online is as simple as tapping the green 'Connect' button, as long as the network is supported. 

4. It is also possible to connect using Secure WiFi (EAP - Extensible Authentication Protocol). Providing you are entitled and have the Secure WiFi profile installed, you will automatically roam onto EAP supported networks ensuring seamless connectivity with increased security."

"connect_faq_answer_10" : "Data updates are applied automatically as you use the app, however if you would like to manually update the network data on your device simply perform the following steps. 

Go to the 'Settings' view and tap 'Update Connect Data' in the 'DATA' section, which will download and install the latest Wi-Fi network information. You can see the date of the last update below 'Update Connect Data'. 

Please note, you must have an active internet connection to be able to update network data."

"connect_faq_answer_11" : "If you are still connected to the Wi-Fi hotspot after selecting 'Disconnect' from within the app, then please select a different Wi-Fi network from within the Device Wi-Fi settings. 

Your connection with the old network will timeout after a short period. If you did not use this app to connect to the hotspot, then this connection cannot be disconnected by this app. Please use the 'Network Selection' screen or Device Wi-Fi Settings to select a different SSID."

"connect_faq_answer_12" : "If you are having continued problems connecting or disconnecting using the app, your customer help desk may request that you send logs to the technical support team for analysis. This will help us diagnose specific hotspot issues. 

When you are requested to do so, please send your logs by using the 'Submit Connection Logs' option in the 'Settings' view. 

Please note, you must have an active internet connection to be able to submit your connection logs."

"connect_faq_answer_2" : "Enable Auto Connect from within the 'Settings' view. 

When this option is enabled, you will be automatically connected to supported hotspots when you select a new Wi-Fi network from within the devices system Wi-Fi settings or if you move within range of a supported network. A notification will appear in the notification bar to let you know you have been connected."
"connect_faq_answer_3" : "There are hundreds of thousands of supported hotspots across the world, including airports, hotels and coffee shops. Use the hotspot finder to locate supported hotspots."

"connect_faq_answer_4" : "Joining a network could not be easier. Simply launch the 'Network Selection' screen (from within the 'Connect' view) by tapping the round button to the right of the screen. 

Look out for a marker next to the list of visible SSIDs, this signifies a supported network. Tap the SSID to join a network."

"connect_faq_answer_5" : "Upon registering and connecting from a device for the first time, the user will be presented with the network services that are associated with their account. 

If you are unsure regarding this, please contact your plan provider. 

Network services can be managed in the application 'Settings'"

"connect_faq_answer_6" : "The Secure WiFi functionality allows users to automatically connect to networks secured with EAP-TTLS (Extensible Authentication Protocol). If a user has service entitlement to EAP, they will be guided through the on-boarding process, after which they will have seamless connectivity to supported network(s)."

"connect_faq_answer_7" : "The VPN feature (Virtual Private Network) allows users secure and seamless connectivity to unsecured networks. 

Intelligent activation will automatically start the VPN functionality when an unsecure network is detected, or VPN can be managed via 'Settings'. 

When enabled a key icon will show within the notification bar."

"connect_faq_answer_8" : "For networks that require a password (or WEP Key), you will be prompted to enter the password before joining. 

A small number of supported networks require a WEP key to be entered when selecting the network from within the Wi-Fi settings. Here are the WEP keys for those networks listed next to the network name (or SSID) 

SSID: MobilePoint 
Key: 696177616b 

SSID: livedoor-web 
Key: elbj63po2pw9j 

SSID: 0448 
Key: a52de42cb6 

SSID: 0033 
Key: a52de42cb6"

"connect_faq_answer_9" : "Go to the 'Settings' view and tap 'Manage Devices' in the 'Account' section. From here you may view a list of all of devices currently registered to your account. 

Your most recently registered devices will be shown at the top of the list. Here you will be able to unregister your current device, or any other devices registered to your account. Tap the row of the device you wish to unregister, then tap 'OK' to confirm the unregistration. 

Unregistering a device will remove all Wi-Fi network information as well as your user credentials from the device. This will happen instantly if you are unregistering the device you are currently using, or the next time this app is launched on any of the other devices you choose to unregister. 

Please note, you must have an active internet connection to be able to unregister devices."

"connect_mngmnt_faq_answer_1" : "Yes, the App now has the capability to automatically connect you to XFINITY WiFi when in a good coverage area. 

For your convenience it is turned ON by default. To turn off this feature go to the 'MANAGE CONNECTIONS' section in 'Settings' and uncheck 'Automatically choose best connection'."

"connect_mngmnt_faq_answer_2" : "Yes, the App now has the capability to turn on/off WiFi based on your past connection history. 

For your convenience it is turned ON by default. To turn off this feature go to the 'MANAGE CONNECTIONS' section in 'Settings' and uncheck 'Turn on WiFi when in range'."

"connect_mngmnt_faq_answer_3" : "The App does not delete/ override any of your existing WiFi networks. It will seamlessly connect your device to any of your known networks. If one is not available, then the App will automatically connect you to XFINITY WiFi anywhere you will have a good experience."

"faq_answer_1" : "There are three ways to find locations using the app: 

Near Me - When the app launches it automatically searches for results around your current location. You are also able to perform a 'Near Me' search by tapping on the 'Near Me' icon which can be found in the top bar of the app. 

Text Search - You are able to search for a geographical location using the search option located in the top bar of the app. Tap on the magnifying glass in order to enter your search term. 

Map Search - To search using the map simply pan or zoom the map to the area in which you wish to find locations, the map will now automatically refresh to show locations in that area. Tapping on a map pin will display an information window showing the location name, tapping on that window will display the full details for that location."

"faq_answer_10" : "Yes, as long as you have less than 5,000 results loaded, you are able to refine your results by selecting the refine button, this icon can be found to the right of the top bar, you can then refine your search by site type or by entering a keyword. Keyword refinements will look for the keyword you enter in the location names of results you have loaded. 

If you have refine your search the refine button will be highlighted to show that refinements are currently active."

"faq_answer_11" : "If you see a problem with the information of a WiFi location, you can tell us by selecting 'Report a Problem' directly from the locations details page. 

Please note, you must have an active internet connection to be able to report a problem and have valid user credentials registered. 

Reported problems will submitted to the Wireless Location Data Service (WLDS) for review. Updates published upon approval."

"faq_answer_2" : "Providing you have already installed an offline dataset you will be able to make searches without an Internet connection. 

To install an offline dataset simply visit the 'Settings' page and select the 'Offline Settings' option within the 'DATA' section. From here you can select which datasets you would like to install. 

Please note that any locations outside of the area that you have datasets installed for will not be searchable when your device is offline."

"faq_answer_3" : "Many settings are configurable within the app, such as units of measurement, map type and offline data. Simply visit the 'Settings' page from within the menu to change these options."

"faq_answer_4" : "If updates are available for your installed offline data and you have an active Internet connection you will be notified when you launch the app. You can choose to install the updates immediately, or leave them until later. Alternatively, you can manually check for updates in the 'Settings' page by selecting the 'Check for Updates' option within the 'DATA' section, your offline data will now be updated. 

Please note that your device will need an active Internet connection in order to update the datasets."

"faq_answer_5" : "Anonymous data is collected to help better manage your experience with the App. No personally identifiable information is stored. 

If you would prefer that we do not collect this information you can disable this within the 'Settings' page by turning off 'Send Information' under the 'ACCOUNT' section."

"faq_answer_6" : "Online searches query a web service to determine your search location and then return locations from an online database. This means the app won't take up much space on your device if you choose to only use the online data. When your device is offline the app will return results from any offline datasets that you have installed. 

For more information about installing datasets please see 'Can I use the app without an Internet connection?' 

Please note that when the app is offline certain functionality such as maps and directions may not be available."

"faq_answer_7" : "We currently support a number of different direction provider apps, and will add support for more in the future. If you have supported apps installed on your device that feature directions functionality they will appear in the selection menu when requesting directions to a hotspot."

"faq_answer_8" : "Yes, if you tap on an item in the search results list a toolbar will appear containing a star icon, tapping this icon will save the hotspot in your favourites list, the star icon is also available on the details view. 

To see your previously saved favourites just visit the 'Favourites' section, this can be found by opening the menu and selecting 'Favourites', or selecting the star icon in the toolbar below the map on a tablet."

"faq_answer_9" : "To share a location, simply tap on an item in the search results list, a toolbar will then appear containing a share icon, selecting this icon will open a menu containing the various share options such as Facebook, Twitter and email, the share icon is also available on the details view. 

Please note that the options contained within the share menu will depend on the apps that you have installed on your device and the accounts you have configured within your device settings."

playstore_details.title: Xfinity WiFi Hotspots
playstore_details.description:
The Xfinity WiFi Hotspots app for Android is available exclusively for Xfinity Internet customers and contains WiFi security features to improve your safety and privacy while using certain Xfinity WiFi hotspots around town. The app also prioritizes your preferred networks and automatically connects you to Xfinity WiFi hotspots when in range. It makes it easy to find Xfinity WiFi hotspots with enhanced search tools and directions. This app is included with your Xfinity Internet service.

Features:
• Prioritize and connect to your secure, saved networks at home and work
• Automatically connect to Xfinity WiFi around town, including secure hotspots where available
• Intelligently turn on WiFi when in range of your saved networks or Xfinity WiFi
• "Near Me" locates all nearby Xfinity WiFi hotspots
• View maps and lists of hotspots, with walking and driving directions
• Create and save your favorite hotspots for easy reference later
• View the business name and business category of hotspot locations
• Find hotspots when not connected, using offline data sets
• Support for Google Street view, if Google Maps is installed

Requirements:
• A WiFi enabled device running Android 4.4 and up 
• Xfinity Internet service (Performance tier and above) 
• Xfinity ID

Xfinity Internet customers:
Look up your existing Xfinity ID (email, mobile phone, or username): xfinity.com/id 
Reset your Xfinity password: xfinity.com/password

Comcast Business Internet customers:
Don’t know your username? https://login.comcast.net/myaccount/bc/lookup
Forgot your password? https://login.comcast.net/myaccount/bc/reset

Xfinity WiFi Hotspots
Xfinity WiFi is the largest, fastest WiFi network in the nation, so there is always a hotspot where you need it most. Xfinity WiFi is included with Xfinity Internet service (Performance tier and above) for no additional charge. Stream what you love around town. Save on your mobile data plan.

Note: This app uses the Device Administrator permission

Learn more about ‘Cal. Civ. Code §1798.135: Do Not Sell My Info’ options at https://www.xfinity.com/privacy/manage-preference
